<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="method">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 °C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine for 7-8 minutes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is endemic to ophiolitic substrates of western Liguria and Toscana (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.7320/FlMedit25SI.007" author="Arrigoni, PV" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B4" refString="Arrigoni, PV, 2015. Contribution to the study of the genus Armeria (Plumbaginaceae) in the Italian peninsula. Flora Mediterranea 25(SI): 7-32. https://doi.org/10.7320/FlMedit25SI.007" title="Contribution to the study of the genus Armeria (Plumbaginaceae) in the Italian peninsula. Flora Mediterranea 25 (SI): 7 - 32." url="https://doi.org/10.7320/FlMedit25SI.007" year="2015">Arrigoni 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The type locality of this species is in Liguria, but very close to the border with Toscana, where the vast majority of populations is found. We report here three counts, one obtained from plants collected in the type locality and two from elsewhere in Toscana. These data confirm the 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 18 chromosome number reported for Impruneta, Firenze (
<bibRefCitation author="Arrigoni, PV" journalOrPublisher="Giornale Botanico Italiano" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="438 - 439" refId="B2" refString="Arrigoni, PV, Giannerini, M, Mori, B, 1976. Contributi citotassonomici e cariologici alla conoscenza di alcune serpentinofite toscane. Giornale Botanico Italiano 110 (6): 438 - 439" title="Contributi citotassonomici e cariologici alla conoscenza di alcune serpentinofite toscane." volume="110" year="1976">Arrigoni et al. 1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Arrigoni, PV" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="137 - 143" refId="B3" refString="Arrigoni, PV, Giannerini, M, Mori, B, 1980. Numeri cromosomici per la flora italiana: 714-721. Informatore Botanico Italiano 12 (2): 137 - 143" title="Numeri cromosomici per la flora italiana: 714 - 721." volume="12" year="1980">1980</bibRefCitation>
). This is also the only known number for the entire genus (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/nph.13191" author="Rice, A" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B24" refString="Rice, A, Glick, L, Abadi, S, Einhorn, M, Kopelman, NM, Salman-Minkov, A, Mayzel, J, Chay, O, Mayrose, I, 2014. The Chromosome Counts Database (CCDB) - a community resource of plant chromosome numbers. New Phytologist 206: 19-26. [accessed 3 December 2021] https://doi.org/10.1111/nph.13191" title="The Chromosome Counts Database (CCDB) - a community resource of plant chromosome numbers. New Phytologist 206: 19 - 26. [accessed 3 December 2021]" url="https://doi.org/10.1111/nph.13191" year="2014">Rice et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
+).
</paragraph>
